title: Johns Hopkins in talks for India campus

description: India successfully test-fired its first hypersonic missile, achieving a speed exceeding five times the speed of sound. The missile, capable of carrying various payloads over 1,500km, marks a significant advancement in India's defense capabilities, positioning the nation among a select group with hypersonic technology.
title: Amid global race, India tests its first hypersonic missile

description: The Chhattisgarh Waqf board has directed all mosques to seek approval for the topic of sermons delivered every Friday. This decision, aimed at preventing political agendas in mosques, requires Mutawallis (caretakers) to submit their sermon topics for approval, ensuring that mosques remain places of worship and not political platforms.
title: Seek nod for Friday sermon topics, waqf board tells Chhattisgarh imams

description: The oil ministry and city gas operators are at odds over CNG price hikes. Operators, facing reduced legacy gas allocations and higher import costs, want to raise prices. However, the government, citing operators' healthy profit margins, finds the proposal politically sensitive ahead of assembly polls.
title: Ahead of Maha, Delhi polls, Centre & city gas cos spar over CNG price

description: Law ministry has drafted legislation to modernize the definition of 'offices of profit,' aiming to prevent the disqualification of Members of Parliament. The bill incorporates recommendations from a parliamentary committee, suggesting exemptions for MPs involved in key government programs like Swachh Bharat Mission and Smart City Mission.
title: Eyeing 'office of profit' tweaks, Centre seeks to replace 1959 law

description: Kailash Gahlot, a senior AAP leader and Delhi government minister, resigned from his positions and the party, citing a drift from core values. Gahlot criticized the AAP's unfulfilled promises, including cleaning the Yamuna River, and alluded to controversies surrounding Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal.
title: In pre-poll blow to AAP, Kailash Gahlot quits party & Delhi Cabinet

description: The bodies of a woman and a girl child were found in Assam's Barak river, following a day of unrest in Manipur sparked by the discovery of six bodies, suspected to be those of missing people from a relief camp.  Mobs in Imphal valley targeted homes of 13 MLAs, vandalizing and setting fire to several properties.
title: Manipur violence; 2 more bodies float down river; homes of MLAs attacked

description: Delhi's air quality plunged to its worst this season, reaching the 'severe plus' category. The Commission for Air Quality Management implemented emergency measures, including halting physical classes for most students and urging work-from-home arrangements. Construction activities, even on crucial projects, are now banned, and vehicular restrictions intensified.
title: ​​Sign of four: GRAP to squeeze Delhi further

description: Hira Devi, an octogenarian from a Uttarakhand ghost village, is set to make her film debut in 'Pyre' at the Tallinn Black Nights International Film Festival. The film, inspired by Devi's own life, tells the story of an elderly couple's love.
title: 80-yr-old who lives alone in a Uttarakhand ghost village is an unlikely film heroine
EPS may merge ADMK with BJP: Udhayanidhi Stalin
PM Modi receives Nigeria's second-highest honour

description: Prajwal Shetty, son of a Congress leader, was arrested for a hit-and-run accident that resulted in the death of 39-year-old Mohammed Hussain. Shetty allegedly hit Hussain's motorcycle with his SUV, causing fatal injuries.  He fled the scene but was later apprehended and released. Police are investigating the incident.
title: Congress neta’s son booked in Karnataka hit-and-run case
Under BJP, Manipur neither 'ek' nor 'safe': Mallikarjun Kharge

description: Clashes erupted in Beldanga, Murshidabad, between two groups following a controversial message displayed at a Kartik Puja pandal, leading to vandalism and disruptions. Police arrested 17 individuals, enforced internet shutdowns, and implemented prohibitory orders to restore order. Despite the tensions, the traditional 'Kartik er Lorai' procession proceeded peacefully.
title: Net shutdown, prohibitory orders after Beldanga clashes

description: NCP chief Sharad Pawar's wife, Pratibha Pawar, and granddaughter, Revati, were briefly prevented from entering the Baramati Hi-Tech Textile Park, chaired by Deputy CM Ajit Pawar's wife. The incident, attributed to miscommunication about a political rally, was resolved after park authorities intervened, allowing them entry.
title: Sharad Pawar's wife stopped at business park tied to Ajit's wife

description: Tensions escalate in the Middle East as Israel conducts airstrikes in Beirut and Gaza, resulting in numerous casualties. Hezbollah's chief spokesman was killed in a targeted strike, prompting retaliatory rocket fire into Israel. The strikes come as ceasefire negotiations are underway, with Lebanon accusing Israel of escalating violence.
title: Hezbollah media chief killed in Israeli strike on Beirut

description: A parliamentary panel is urging the Indian government to address issues with the "creamy layer" policy for Other Backward Classes (OBCs). The panel highlights the lack of consistent "equivalence of posts" across government institutions, leading to discrepancies in how the policy is applied. They argue that the current system disadvantages OBC candidates from certain backgrounds and contradicts existing guidelines.
title: House panel on OBCs likely to push for 'equivalence of posts'

description: Meghalaya's ruling NPP withdrew support from the BJP-led Manipur government, citing chief minister Biren Singh's failure to curb the ongoing violence.  NPP's withdrawal doesn't impact BJP's majority.  Former CM Okram Ibobi Singh demanded Prime Minister Modi's intervention, threatening mass resignations by non-NDA MLAs if the situation doesn't improve.
title: 'Biren Singh failed': NPP withdraws support to BJP govt in Manipur

description: The Commission for Air Quality Management has enforced Stage-IV (Severe+) GRAP actions from November 18 due to deteriorating air quality. Delhi CM Atishi announced that all schools will shift to online classes, except for Classes 10 and 12. Emergency measures like college closures and an odd-even vehicle rule are under consideration. Parents should check for updates with schools.
title: Delhi air pollution: Online classes for all students, except class 10 & 12

description: Delhi NCR is facing severe air pollution, prompting the Commission for Air Quality Management to enforce GRAP Stage 4.  The stringent measures include banning truck entry (except essential goods), halting construction activities, and urging schools to consider online classes.  With a daily AQI exceeding 450, the government advises citizens to stay indoors and minimize outdoor activities.
title: GRAP-4 imposed in Delhi-NCR; what's allowed and what's not

description: Pakistan's Telecommunication Authority initiated a registration process for VPNs following a nationwide ban on unregistered ones.  The government claims the ban targets militant groups, but critics view it as an attempt to stifle dissent amidst online criticism of the military and the blocking of platforms like X.
title: Amid Net censorship, Pakistan offers regulated VPNs

description: Bangladesh's interim leader, Muhammad Yunus, announced his government's intention to extradite former Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina from India to face prosecution for alleged crimes during her rule, including casualties during the August protests that led to her departure. Yunus pledged to hold elections after implementing reforms.
title: Bangladesh will seek extradition of former PM Hasina: Yunus

description: Three engineering students from Mysuru tragically drowned in the swimming pool of a Mangaluru resort. The victims, all in their early twenties, were found at the deep end of the pool, which lacked proper depth markings and a lifeguard. Police are investigating the resort for negligence, as CCTV footage contradicts their claim of having staff present during the incident.
title: 3 girls of Karnataka engineering college drown in resort pool

description: A new study reveals that nearly 28% of India's subsidized grains, intended for the poor, are lost to leakage, costing the government an estimated Rs 69,108 crore. While digitalization has helped, researchers urge for reforms including direct cash transfers to combat corruption and ensure food security.
title: PDS leaks costing exchequer Rs 69,000 crore a year: Report

description: Survivors of the Chooralmala-Mundakkai landslides in Kerala are escalating their protests after the RBI rejected their loan waiver requests. Despite meeting with RBI officials, residents continue to face pressure from banks and NBFCs for loan repayments, leaving them struggling to rebuild their lives without income or jobs.
title: Wayanad survivors to step up stir as RBI refuses to ask banks to waive loans

description: CBSE schools in Kochi are replacing traditional marks and grades with emojis and stars for students in kindergarten through Class II. This shift aligns with the New Education Policy's emphasis on holistic development, replacing exams with project work and activities that assess various skills.
title: CBSE schools in Kochi ditch marks for emojis & stars

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi praised the film 'The Sabarmati Report' for revealing the truth about the 2002 Godhra train burning, sparking debate about the incident's history and the film's portrayal. The film claims to offer a fresh perspective on the tragedy based on court documents and eyewitness accounts, challenging established narratives.
title: 'Truth coming out': PM Modi hails film on Godhra train burning

description: An assistant professor in Telangana is under investigation for allegedly getting a first-year medical student's head tonsured. This was done to resolve a dispute between seniors and juniors regarding the student's hairstyle. While the professor claims he was defusing a tense situation and the student went to the barbershop willingly, the incident has sparked an inquiry by the health minister.
title: Medical college professor in trouble after getting boy to tonsure head

description: Right-wing groups in Udaipur disrupted the 9th Udaipur Film Festival, forcing organizers to relocate the event to a makeshift tent. Protesters objected to screenings about Palestinian children and the late professor G N Saibaba, labeling them as promoting "jihadist and Maoist ideologies."
title: Udaipur film fest disrupted over movies on Palestine, GN Saibaba

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Nigerian President Bola Tinubu pledged to strengthen their strategic partnership during Modi's visit to Nigeria.  They committed to collaborating on combating terrorism, advancing the interests of the Global South, and expanding cooperation in areas like defense, energy, and trade.
title: PM Modi, Nigerian president pledge to fight terrorism & radicalisation

description: Mumbai police arrested two more individuals, Salman Vohra and Akash Deep Gill, in connection with the murder of NCP leader Baba Siddique. Vohra is accused of handling the finances and transferring funds to the shooters, while Gill allegedly acted as a coordinator. Police investigations revealed that the gang received approximately Rs 8 lakh from Canada via hawala channels.
title: Man whose account was used to pay Siddique’s killers held

description: A fire erupted in the overcrowded neonatal intensive care unit of Maharani Laxmibai Medical College in Jhansi, India, resulting in the tragic deaths of ten infants.  The blaze, attributed to an overheated oxygen concentrator, was exacerbated by overcrowding and continuous operation of life-support equipment.  Investigations are underway to determine the extent of safety lapses and potential negligence.
title: Continuous running of life-support devices led to Jhansi hospital fire: Probe
Yogi Adityanath sticks to 'batenge toh...' slogan amid row

description: Karnataka's chief minister Siddaramaiah has refuted claims that the state is removing BPL cardholders to fund its guarantee schemes. He clarified that only "ineligible" beneficiaries, including taxpayers and government employees, will be shifted to APL cards. This decision comes as the state grapples with a high number of BPL cardholders, raising concerns about resource allocation.
title: K’taka CM allays fears after row over plan to trim BPL card list
'Mess with anyone but me': Sharad Pawar vows to defeat Ajit faction in a ‘big’ way

description: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) refuted claims of Jason Gillespie's departure as head coach, confirming his commitment through the South Africa series. Despite Gillespie's successes, including victories against England and Australia, rumors circulated about his potential replacement with Aaqib Javed. This situation highlights the PCB's history of frequent coaching changes, raising concerns about stability ahead of major tournaments.
title: 'Strongly refutes': PCB dismisses reports on Gillespie's removal

description: Jharkhand Chief Minister Hemant Soren pledged to introduce a state award named after tribal leaders Birsa Munda and Sido-Kanhu if his alliance wins the upcoming assembly elections. This announcement, made on Saturday, follows the central government's recent tribute to Birsa Munda, which Soren deemed insufficient.
title: Hemant Soren to name top state award after Birsa Munda, Sido-Kanhu

description: Uddhav Thackeray, in a final MVA rally, criticized PM Modi for invoking Balasaheb Thackeray's name for votes. He accused the MahaYuti government of favoring Adani and threatened to reverse decisions benefiting the group if MVA is elected. Thackeray also pledged to protect Mumbai's status and BMC's autonomy, alleging the current government's actions undermine them.
title: On MVA return, will first scrap pro-Adani decisions: Uddhav Thackeray

description: An 18-year-old medical student in Gujarat tragically died after allegedly being forced to stand for hours during a ragging incident. Fellow students claim seniors subjected their group to prolonged standing and questioning. The college and police have initiated investigations, promising disciplinary action against any seniors found culpable.
title: 1st-year MBBS student dies after ragging at Gujarat college

description: Indian business tycoon Harsh Goenka playfully poked fun at Pakistani cricketer Mohammad Rizwan's unclear response to a reporter's question about India's refusal to participate in the ICC Men's Champions Trophy in Pakistan.
title: Harsh Goenka 'seeks help' to understand this interview of Pak cricket team captain

description: In Pakur, a district bordering Bangladesh, accusations of infiltration and land grabbing fuel tensions ahead of elections. However, residents maintain that long-standing traditions of interfaith marriages and land arrangements are being misconstrued. While authorities acknowledge attempts to cross the border, they emphasize that these are primarily related to smuggling, not permanent settlement.
title: Bangladeshi 'infiltrators' poll pitch leaves Jharkhand district on edge

description: The Election Commission directed the removal of a controversial video from BJP Jharkhand's social media platforms following complaints from the Congress and JMM, who alleged it spread misinformation and aimed to incite hatred. The EC issued a notice to BJP Jharkhand seeking an explanation for the alleged Model Code of Conduct violation.
title: EC directs Jharkhand BJP to take down controversial social media post

description: Manipur is experiencing escalating ethnic violence, leading to numerous deaths and widespread unrest.  The National People's Party withdrew support from the BJP-led government, citing its failure to control the situation.  Congress leaders offered to resign if it would help restore peace, highlighting the dire situation.
title: Manipur violence: NPP breaks alliance with BJP, protesters target leaders

description: The Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM) has implemented Stage-IV (Severe+) actions under the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP) in Delhi-NCR, effective November 18.  These measures, including transitioning some school grades to online learning and implementing a 50% workforce policy for offices, aim to combat worsening air quality as winter approaches.
title: Delhi air pollution: GRAP-4 curbs imposed, all classes except 10, 12 go online

description: Prince Harry's US residency is under scrutiny following Donald Trump's election victory. The Heritage Foundation believes Trump's stance on immigration increases their chances of accessing Harry's visa records, potentially revealing drug use disclosures. Legal experts suggest deportation is possible, with Trump holding the authority to remove Harry or potentially pardon him as a gesture towards King Charles.
title: Trump might not deport Prince Harry as 'favor to King Charles'

description: A food van near Delhi's Vishwavidyalaya metro station caught fire on Sunday morning, sending plumes of black smoke into the air. The Delhi Fire Services extinguished the blaze, which broke out around 10:55 am, by noon. No injuries were reported. Police suspect an electrical fault in the cooking equipment caused the fire.
title: Video: Massive fire at popular food van near Delhi Metro station
Woman killed, 11 injured on way to picnic after speeding vehicle overturns

description: The National People's Party (NPP) has withdrawn its support from the BJP-led Manipur government, blaming its failure to quell the violence and restore peace in the state. The move follows a recent surge in violence, including attacks on government officials' residences, prompting curfews and internet shutdowns.
title: NPP withdraws support from Manipur govt citing failure to resolve crisis

description: Union home minister Amit Shah reviewed the security situation in Manipur on Sunday after fresh violence erupted. He directed officials to take all necessary steps to restore peace. The unrest, marked by attacks on legislators' homes and killings in Jiribam, follows ethnic strife since May 2023, which has left over 220 dead and thousands displaced.
title: Manipur violence: Amit Shah holds key meet with top officials

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi was awarded Nigeria's second-highest national honor, the Grand Commander of the Order of the Niger.  President Bola Ahmed Tinubu presented the award, recognizing Modi as the second recipient after Queen Elizabeth. Modi expressed gratitude and pledged to strengthen the strategic partnership between India and Nigeria.
title: Watch: PM Modi receives Nigeria's second highest national award

description: Matthew Hayden believes India's recent Test series loss to New Zealand could be beneficial. He says playing long-format cricket gives India a preparation advantage for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. The series against Australia starts on November 22 in Perth. The teams will then play in Adelaide, Brisbane, Melbourne, and Sydney. The final Test match will be in Sydney on January 3.
title: Hayden identifies India's 'advantage' after 3-0 whitewash to NZ

description: Four months after a devastating landslide in Wayanad, affected residents are yet to receive compensation from the Rs 658.42 crore collected in the CMDRF. While both the state and central governments debate over aid approvals, the lack of disbursement raises concerns about the timely allocation of relief funds, leaving many families struggling to rebuild their lives.
title: Wayanad landslide: No funds disbursed yet from Rs 658 crore in CMDRF

description: With Rohit Sharma and Shubman Gill unavailable for the first Test against Australia, India has called up Devdutt Padikkal as batting backup. Jasprit Bumrah will captain the team in Rohit's absence. Additionally,  uncapped pacer Harshit Rana may make his Test debut in Perth, having impressed during recent matches and net sessions.
title: Padikkal to stay back, Rana likely to make debut in Perth

description: Iran's Supreme Leader, Ali Khamenei, reportedly chose his son, Mojtaba, as his successor during a secret meeting of the Assembly of Experts. The decision, driven by Khamenei's declining health, was allegedly made under pressure and kept secret to avoid public backlash. Mojtaba Khamenei, known for his role in suppressing past protests, has been gradually gaining influence within the regime.
title: Ali Khamenei’s son set to take over as Iran's supreme leader: Report

description: Delhi chief minister Atishi will retain all departments previously overseen by Kailash Gahlot, who resigned from both the Delhi Cabinet and the Aam Aadmi Party (AAP). Gahlot cited dissatisfaction with the party's direction, specifically mentioning controversies like the 'Sheeshmahal' issue and a perceived shift in priorities from public service to internal political agendas.
title: Kailash Gahlot resigns: Delhi CM Atishi to handle his departments
'Truth is coming out': PM Modi praises 'The Sabarmati Report' film

description: Senior AAP leader and Delhi minister Kailash Gahlot resigned from the party, citing disillusionment and internal challenges. While the BJP praised his decision, AAP alleged that pressure from central agencies led to Gahlot's resignation. This development comes months before the Delhi assembly polls and is expected to impact the political landscape.
title: Kailash Gahlot resigns: BJP calls it bold step; AAP claims conspiracy

description: BJP president J P Nadda accused the JMM-led Jharkhand government of harboring Bangladeshi infiltrators, facilitating their acquisition of official documents, and even land ownership. He vowed to introduce legislation to prevent land ownership for offspring of infiltrators who marry tribal women. Nadda also criticized the government's alleged corruption and divisive policies, predicting their downfall in the upcoming elections.
title: Intel report says Soren govt gave shelter to Bangladeshis: Nadda

description: Union minister Nitin Gadkari dismissed Rahul Gandhi's criticisms of PM Modi as irresponsible and not to be taken seriously.  Gadkari emphasized the BJP's focus on development and unity, downplaying the significance of the 'batenge toh katenge' slogan and expressing confidence in the BJP-led alliance's prospects in the upcoming Maharashtra assembly elections.
title: 'Speaks irresponsibly': Nitin Gadkari on Rahul's 'memory loss' remark at PM Modi

description: Pakistani TikTok star Imsha Rehman deactivated her social media accounts after allegedly private videos were leaked online. This incident follows a similar event last month involving influencer Minahil Malik, sparking debate about privacy and online harassment.
title: Who is Imsha Rehman the Pakistani influencer whose obscene video leaked online

description: Attorney Tony Buzbee is pursuing legal action against attendees of Sean "Diddy" Combs' alleged "freak-off parties," sending demand letters to numerous A-list celebrities. Buzbee argues their presence and silence make them complicit in alleged illegal activities.
title: A-list celebrities at Diddy's 'Freak-Off Parties' face legal pressure, read here

description: The Buffalo Bills are preparing to host the undefeated Kansas City Chiefs, with Taylor Swift's potential attendance adding another layer of intrigue. Swift's previous experience with the Bills Mafia during last season's playoffs, described as "ruthless" by those close to her, has raised concerns about her reception.
title: Taylor Swift may have no desire to return to Higmark Stadium to support Travis Kelce

description: Uday Kotak, a veteran in financial services, has voiced his concerns about the potential political ramifications of Quick Commerce's (Q-Com) impact on traditional retailers in India. Kotak's remarks follow the recent successful listing of Swiggy, a prominent player in the Indian Q-Com market.
title: Uday Kotak's 'warning' about Swiggy, Zomato & other quick commerce cos
